class:: SimpleReverbCh
summary:: Stereo reverb based on the chowdsp_utils SimpleReverb example
categories:: UGens>Effects
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

SimpleReverbCh follows the `SimpleReverb` example from chowdsp_utils. The reverb is built around an 8-line stereo feedback delay network with separate low- and high-frequency T60 control, a diffuser ahead of the network, and small internal modulation to keep repeated trajectories from locking too obviously. In state-space terms the decay is controlled by the feedback matrix, the delay lengths, and the frequency-dependent damping filters applied inside the loop.

This is not meant to emulate a specific acoustic room in detail. It is a compact algorithmic reverb that can move from small synthetic ambience to a more spacious and polished tail, with the modulation helping the decay feel less metallic and less static on sustained material.

definitionlist::
## diffusionTime: || front-end diffusion time in milliseconds, intended range `10..1000`
## fdnDelay: || base FDN delay time in milliseconds, intended range `50..500`
## fdnT60Low: || low-frequency T60 in milliseconds, intended range `100..5000`
## fdnT60High: || high-frequency T60 in milliseconds, intended range `100..5000`
## modAmount: || normalized FDN delay modulation amount in `0..1`
## dryWet: || dry/wet mix in `0..1`
::

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::inL
Left input.

argument::inR
Right input.

argument::diffusionTime
Front-end diffusion time in milliseconds.

argument::fdnDelay
Base FDN delay time in milliseconds.

argument::fdnT60Low
Low-frequency decay time in milliseconds.

argument::fdnT60High
High-frequency decay time in milliseconds.

argument::modAmount
Normalized modulation amount.

argument::dryWet
Dry/wet mix.


